      <pubDate>Thu, 04 Jun 2026 18:00:00 +0000</pubDate>
      <description>&lt;div&gt;&lt;img src="https://hb.imgix.net/55b3d3478ed4787615534a162a7efbcc49f03cb5.png?auto=compress,format&amp;h=340&amp;w=1200&amp;s=ad85bbce8c551f4d31b4b4bab2a14e2f"&gt;&lt;img src="https://hb.imgix.net/3e596aa3d0fecc922ecea06e1852e2e675592395.jpg?auto=compress,format&amp;fit=crop&amp;h=600&amp;w=1200&amp;s=3da15a6b5b1e3db622e14cb264741ccf"&gt;&lt;h2&gt;Unlock your creative side with Unity&lt;/h2&gt;&lt;p&gt;Your new career in game development is only a click away with The 2026 Learn Unity Game Development Bundle! No prior knowledge is needed for this curated collection of lessons from GameDev.tv—just come prepared with a curious mind and a passion for gaming. Get started today and create your own RPG, 2D adventure, and more with courses like &lt;em&gt;Unity Turn Based Strategy Course&lt;/em&gt; and &lt;em&gt;Unity Real Time Strategy Course&lt;/em&gt;. Get the expert instruction you need from pros in the field, and help support Trees, Water &amp; People with your purchase! &lt;br/&gt;&lt;br/&gt;&lt;span style="color: #ef9741;"&gt;Keys expire. All titles should be redeemed before June 25th, 2027. &lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt;&lt;ul&gt;&lt;li&gt;&lt;a href="#0"&gt;Pay $5 to unlock!&lt;/a&gt;&lt;/li&gt;&lt;ul&gt;&lt;li&gt;&lt;a href="#unitygamefeelcourse"&gt;Unity Game Feel Course&lt;/a&gt;&lt;/li&gt;&lt;li&gt;&lt;a href="#fromblendertounitycourse"&gt;From Blender to Unity&lt;/a&gt;&lt;/li&gt;&lt;/ul&gt;&lt;li&gt;&lt;a href="#bt20"&gt;Pay $20 or more to also unlock!&lt;/a&gt;&lt;/li&gt;&lt;ul&gt;&lt;li&gt;&lt;a href="#leveldesignfundamentalscourse_getgoodatmakinggamelevelsthatwork"&gt;Level Design Fundamentals Course&lt;/a&gt;&lt;/li&gt;&lt;li&gt;&lt;a href="#unityproceduralgenerationcourse"&gt;Unity Procedural Generation Course&lt;/a&gt;&lt;/li&gt;&lt;/ul&gt;&lt;li&gt;&lt;a href="#bt25"&gt;Pay $25 or more to also unlock!&lt;/a&gt;&lt;/li&gt;&lt;ul&gt;&lt;li&gt;&lt;a href="#programmingdesignpatternsforunitycourse"&gt;Programming Design Patterns For Unity Course&lt;/a&gt;&lt;/li&gt;&lt;li&gt;&lt;a href="#unityshadergraphcourse"&gt;Unity Shader Graph Course&lt;/a&gt;&lt;/li&gt;&lt;li&gt;&lt;a href="#unityturnbasedstrategycourse"&gt;Unity Turn Based Strategy Course&lt;/a&gt;&lt;/li&gt;&lt;li&gt;&lt;a href="#unitymultiplayercodingandnetworkingngo"&gt;Unity Multiplayer Coding &amp; Networking NGO Course&lt;/a&gt;&lt;/li&gt;&lt;li&gt;&lt;a href="#unity2drpg_completecombatsystemcourse"&gt;Unity 2D RPG: Complete Combat System Course&lt;/a&gt;&lt;/li&gt;&lt;li&gt;&lt;a href="#unity25dturn-basedrpgcourse"&gt;Unity 2.5D Turn-Based RPG&lt;/a&gt;&lt;/li&gt;&lt;li&gt;&lt;a href="#unityrealtimestrategycourse"&gt;Unity Real Time Strategy Course&lt;/a&gt;&lt;/li&gt;&lt;li&gt;&lt;a href="#completeunity3dcdevelopercourse"&gt;Complete Unity 3D C# Developer Course&lt;/a&gt;&lt;/li&gt;&lt;/ul&gt;&lt;/ul&gt;&lt;h2 id="0"&gt;Pay $5 to unlock!&lt;/h2&gt;&lt;h3 id="unitygamefeelcourse"&gt;&lt;a id="unitygamefeelcourse" href="https://youtu.be/zloOv5LS4xY"&gt;Unity Game Feel Course&lt;/a&gt;&lt;/h3&gt;&lt;img&gt;&lt;img src="https://hb.imgix.net/ae5f603b839f512cf09ab51e3cdd7a4f502553ab.jpg?auto=compress,format&amp;fit=clip&amp;h=350&amp;w=600&amp;s=199b411f7cef4914d105c22aa65efeb0"&gt;&lt;br&gt;&lt;p&gt;Ever feel that your game just doesn’t feel quite right?&lt;/p&gt;&lt;p&gt;Learn how to fix that by implementing a bunch of fun systems, mechanics and effects to enhance the way your game feels from a player perspective!&lt;/p&gt;&lt;p&gt;Building upon solid C# and Unity foundations, it’s time for you to level up.&lt;/p&gt;&lt;p&gt;Increase your C# understanding, learning how to implement things like a struct, centralized input, interfaces, and several game design patterns.&lt;/p&gt;&lt;p&gt;And expand on your Unity knowledge by learning screen shake, post-processing effects, 2D lighting, particle effects, tilemap prefabs, masking, Unity events, and much more!&lt;/p&gt;&lt;p&gt;Plus, you’ll even build an expandable Audio Manager system that can be used in other mid-sized scalable projects.&lt;/p&gt;&lt;p&gt;You’ll start with a 2D side scroller shooter base template and expand on it to get things feeling the way they should.&lt;/p&gt;&lt;p&gt;Make a game that “feels” fun to play with a clean and snappy player controller, a gun that’s fun to shoot, audio and screen visuals to give your player feedback, as well as animations to bring everything together.&lt;/p&gt;&lt;p&gt;Grab the bundle today and get your game feeling just right!&lt;/p&gt;&lt;h3 id="fromblendertounitycourse"&gt;&lt;a id="fromblendertounitycourse" href="https://youtu.be/QQQmXENToqU"&gt;From Blender to Unity&lt;/a&gt;&lt;/h3&gt;&lt;img&gt;&lt;img&gt;&lt;br&gt;&lt;p&gt;Get your Blender characters working in Unity - clean, optimised and game-ready.&lt;/p&gt;&lt;p&gt;You’ll build a solid export workflow for characters, props and animations, baking textures, setting up LODs, rigging with Rigify and animating with the Non-Linear Animation Editor.&lt;/p&gt;&lt;p&gt;Export character actions that just work inside Unity, no broken materials or import weirdness.&lt;/p&gt;&lt;p&gt;Perfect for devs and artists ready to bring their own characters into the engine. Grab the bundle and get building.&lt;/p&gt;&lt;h2 id="bt20"&gt;Pay $20 or more to also unlock!&lt;/h2&gt;&lt;h3 id="leveldesignfundamentalscourse_getgoodatmakinggamelevelsthatwork"&gt;&lt;a id="leveldesignfundamentalscourse_getgoodatmakinggamelevelsthatwork" href="https://youtu.be/42MirGlEv78"&gt;Level Design Fundamentals Course&lt;/a&gt;&lt;/h3&gt;&lt;img&gt;&lt;img src="https://hb.imgix.net/560fd8576b5c649e9f724a200d4df11eda61bd3f.jpg?auto=compress,format&amp;fit=clip&amp;h=350&amp;w=600&amp;s=6be47c350f4748df8ba541775ff28de3"&gt;&lt;br&gt;&lt;p&gt;My levels feel... fine. But fine isn't fun.""&lt;/p&gt; &lt;p&gt;If that hits close to home, this course is for you. Good level design isn't magic - it's a craft. And once you learn how it works, you'll see it everywhere.&lt;/p&gt; &lt;p&gt;We dig into real levels from real games to reverse-engineer what makes them stick. The tension, the pacing, the moment a level just gets you - none of that happened by accident. Someone designed every beat on purpose. This course shows you how they did it, and how you can too.&lt;/p&gt; &lt;p&gt;You'll walk away with design frameworks, layout patterns you can swipe for your own games, a 10-step workflow, and greyboxing techniques that work in the real world - not just in theory.&lt;/p&gt; &lt;p&gt;Whether you're heading into your first game jam or building your dream indie project, stop hoping your levels turn out okay. Start designing them to be great.fix description&lt;/p&gt;&lt;h3 id="unityproceduralgenerationcourse"&gt;&lt;a id="unityproceduralgenerationcourse" href="https://youtu.be/BlXCtnXmxjM"&gt;Unity Procedural Generation Course&lt;/a&gt;&lt;/h3&gt;&lt;img&gt;&lt;img src="https://hb.imgix.net/0b2aee1ec57713b064a9001028553aa0b996b292.jpg?auto=compress,format&amp;fit=clip&amp;h=350&amp;w=600&amp;s=0d1044f763ab7856b110e16097a217d0"&gt;&lt;br&gt;&lt;p&gt;Want to build infinite game levels that stay fresh every time?&lt;/p&gt;&lt;p&gt;Learn to code your own procedural dungeons with hallways, rooms and just the right amount of chaos.&lt;/p&gt;&lt;p&gt;Turn 2D layouts into full 3D scenes with Marching Squares and power it all with Scriptable Objects.&lt;/p&gt;&lt;p&gt;Add runtime NavMesh so players and enemies can actually get around without faceplanting into walls.&lt;/p&gt;&lt;p&gt;Spawn loot, baddies and decorations using rules that keep things interesting (and not super samey).&lt;/p&gt;&lt;p&gt;You’ll level up your C# skills too, with advanced techniques that make your code lean and mean.&lt;/p&gt;&lt;p&gt;Perfect for devs who know their way around Unity and want to create replayable worlds.&lt;/p&gt;&lt;p&gt;Dive into the bundle and start generating awesome levels on the fly now!&lt;/p&gt;&lt;h2 id="bt25"&gt;Pay $25 or more to also unlock!&lt;/h2&gt;&lt;h3 id="programmingdesignpatternsforunitycourse"&gt;&lt;a id="programmingdesignpatternsforunitycourse" href="https://youtu.be/2IKMw6b8YaI"&gt;Programming Design Patterns For Unity Course&lt;/a&gt;&lt;/h3&gt;&lt;img&gt;&lt;img src="https://hb.imgix.net/234977591e5ba8a9e019f6c9c6fe79febed46bee.jpg?auto=compress,format&amp;fit=clip&amp;h=350&amp;w=600&amp;s=f68ba4530897de1604efc231e3d12e35"&gt;&lt;br&gt;&lt;p&gt;Want to take your coding to the next level? Learning how to apply programming best practices to your Unity projects will help!&lt;/p&gt;&lt;p&gt;Do you ever wonder why your code has so many bugs or find yourself perplexed by code you wrote months ago?&lt;/p&gt;&lt;p&gt;Maybe you've heard of Programming Patterns but don't understand when to use them, or you want to know how to actually implement these Patterns in Unity?&lt;/p&gt;&lt;p&gt;This course covers fundamental programming best practices (including how to write clean, maintainable code), what problems to solve with Programming Patterns, how to write common Patterns in Unity and how Programming Patterns implement best practices.&lt;/p&gt;&lt;p&gt;You'll need a strong understanding of basic C# programming (classes, methods, ifs, loops) and some familiarity with more advanced concepts (inheritance, interfaces, events). And don’t worry if you don’t know this stuff at the moment, we cover all of these topics in the other courses in this bundle.&lt;/p&gt;&lt;p&gt;If you’re ready to code better, this is the course for you!&lt;/p&gt;&lt;h3 id="unityshadergraphcourse"&gt;&lt;a id="unityshadergraphcourse" href="https://youtu.be/sgH4aDEaQkY"&gt;Unity Shader Graph Course&lt;/a&gt;&lt;/h3&gt;&lt;img&gt;&lt;img src="https://hb.imgix.net/e2545f68bfe810d7a9e609bf0d799078e013811a.jpg?auto=compress,format&amp;fit=clip&amp;h=350&amp;w=600&amp;s=709183bcb1ba6f2e1a46fb296657745a"&gt;&lt;br&gt;&lt;p&gt;Unlock the magic of Unity Shader Graph and create visuals that’ll make your players say “Wow!” Dive into our course and master this powerful tool to craft stunning, dynamic effects for your games—no art degree needed.&lt;/p&gt;&lt;p&gt;In this course, you’ll learn to design immersive materials, jaw-dropping lighting, and gameplay-enhancing effects with Shader Graph. From procedural textures that add rich detail to custom lighting that brings your scenes to life, you’ll level up your visual storytelling skills and create effects that truly pop.&lt;/p&gt;&lt;p&gt;Perfect for both beginners and pros, this hands-on, project-based course guides you through each step with high-quality tutorials and practical exercises. Let’s make your games unforgettable—grab this bundle and get ready to wow!&lt;/p&gt;&lt;h3 id="unityturnbasedstrategycourse"&gt;&lt;a id="unityturnbasedstrategycourse" href="https://youtu.be/OKU7Px5bBn4"&gt;Unity Turn Based Strategy Course&lt;/a&gt;&lt;/h3&gt;&lt;img&gt;&lt;img src="https://hb.imgix.net/49063ed8f1e855b1eaf2f3fedac03ac3b6b39e86.jpg?auto=compress,format&amp;fit=clip&amp;h=350&amp;w=600&amp;s=e183524b4e9f7b2c8642ac11039dab6c"&gt;&lt;br&gt;&lt;p&gt;Are you looking to level up your game development skills and take your projects to the next level?&lt;/p&gt;&lt;p&gt;Want to make your own turn-based strategy game, similar to XCOM or Final Fantasy Tactics?* &lt;/p&gt;&lt;p&gt;This is the course for you!&lt;/p&gt;&lt;p&gt;In this course, you’ll take your skills from beginner to advanced, learn to manage and organise a complex project. You’ll create a custom Grid System and learn advanced Programming concepts, such as; C# generics, C# events, custom structs, enemy AI, A* Pathfinding and much more!!&lt;/p&gt;&lt;p&gt;* Even if you’re not interested in turn-based strategy games, these skills are super transferable to other types of games.&lt;/p&gt;&lt;p&gt;We’re really excited to have teamed up with YouTuber Code Monkey, to bring you this awesome Unity content.   &lt;/p&gt;&lt;h3 id="unitymultiplayercodingandnetworkingngo"&gt;&lt;a id="unitymultiplayercodingandnetworkingngo" href="https://youtu.be/JRuVFdI_sg4"&gt;Unity Multiplayer Coding &amp; Networking NGO Course&lt;/a&gt;&lt;/h3&gt;&lt;img&gt;&lt;img src="https://hb.imgix.net/251c89d488f4274f03c45aa35a435e1a8bc3a62f.jpg?auto=compress,format&amp;fit=clip&amp;h=350&amp;w=600&amp;s=2c4ad84c219bfe1ea7556520dcdb48ef"&gt;&lt;br&gt;&lt;p&gt;Ready to make your own large scale game that supports dozens of players?&lt;/p&gt;&lt;p&gt;Learn to build an online game using the latest and greatest framework from Unity, which makes it easy to build multiplayer games (and saves time!)&lt;/p&gt;&lt;p&gt;From building the core gameplay, to taking your game online, to making it deployable as a dedicated server and learning to integrate matchmaking. You'll do it all! Unity is making the process easier than ever with its new Netcode For GameObjects (NGO) framework.&lt;/p&gt;&lt;p&gt;You’ll make a multiplayer top-down shooter, you can play with dozens of people over the internet. And learn how to deploy a dedicated server with matchmaking!&lt;/p&gt;&lt;p&gt;We’re making a .io style game (like slither.io and agar.io), that can accommodate dozens of players. Through that process you’ll build the skills to make your own competitive or cooperative multiplayer game in any genre that interests you.&lt;/p&gt;&lt;p&gt;Jump in and start creating your own multiplayer game now. You’ll be playing it with your friends in no time!&lt;/p&gt;&lt;h3 id="unity2drpg_completecombatsystemcourse"&gt;&lt;a id="unity2drpg_completecombatsystemcourse" href="https://youtu.be/OSXieQQrjJg"&gt;Unity 2D RPG: Complete Combat System Course&lt;/a&gt;&lt;/h3&gt;&lt;img&gt;&lt;img src="https://hb.imgix.net/984909baafd79b8d9e96fef345e40bb7c18774ca.jpg?auto=compress,format&amp;fit=clip&amp;h=350&amp;w=600&amp;s=eeb480d19a6abd83b147d7ae398d3d4d"&gt;&lt;br&gt;&lt;p&gt;Ready to create your own classic 2D top-down RPG game in Unity?&lt;/p&gt;&lt;p&gt; Building an RPG is an amazing way to level-up your game development skills, so grab your magic staff, watch out for projectile grapes and start improving your game development right now! &lt;/p&gt;&lt;p&gt; Role Playing Games can be complex to create, with many interacting gameplay systems. We’ve made it easy for you, this course teaches you step-by-step how to make the foundations of any good RPG - from scratch!&lt;/p&gt;&lt;p&gt; You'll learn 2D top-down movement, combining C# and animator components, a combat system with multiple weapons, scene management &amp;amp; scene persistence, tilemap, rule tiles, animated tiles, scene workflow and much more!&lt;/p&gt;&lt;h3 id="unity25dturn-basedrpgcourse"&gt;&lt;a id="unity25dturn-basedrpgcourse" href="https://youtu.be/HosxQuSM2OU"&gt;Unity 2.5D Turn-Based RPG&lt;/a&gt;&lt;/h3&gt;&lt;img&gt;&lt;img&gt;&lt;br&gt;&lt;p&gt;Ready to unlock the secrets of 2.5D turn-based games with Unity and C#? Whether you’re just stepping into game dev or levelling up, this course has you covered.&lt;/p&gt;&lt;p&gt;You’ll create your own turn-based combat system that’s both fun to play and super flexible, thanks to the magic of scriptable objects. Dive deep into Unity’s tools—from Cinemachine for cinematic flair, to particle effects that add major pizzazz!&lt;/p&gt;&lt;p&gt;Learn to craft immersive worlds with 3D models and sprites, bringing characters to life as they leap into battle. We’ll walk you through building a scalable battle system, making it easy to navigate.&lt;/p&gt;&lt;p&gt;Perfect for beginner to beginner+ devs, this course turns your game ideas into real, playable worlds. Join us and start crafting your dream games!&lt;/p&gt;&lt;h3 id="unityrealtimestrategycourse"&gt;&lt;a id="unityrealtimestrategycourse" href="https://youtu.be/M4enqMidRpU"&gt;Unity Real Time Strategy Course&lt;/a&gt;&lt;/h3&gt;&lt;img&gt;&lt;img&gt;&lt;br&gt;&lt;p&gt;Ever wanted to build your own RTS but didn’t know where to start?&lt;/p&gt;&lt;p&gt;This course teaches you how to create the full package, units, buildings, fog of war, upgrades and more.&lt;/p&gt;&lt;p&gt;You’ll wrangle behaviour trees for smarter AI, set up scalable systems and ditch the spaghetti code for clean, config-driven goodness.&lt;/p&gt;&lt;p&gt;Use ScriptableObjects and event buses to keep your game tidy (and future you sane).&lt;/p&gt;&lt;p&gt;Add new units and upgrades straight from the editor - no more hard-coded chaos.&lt;/p&gt;&lt;p&gt;If you know your way around Unity and C#, this is your chance to level up and go full commander mode.&lt;/p&gt;&lt;p&gt;Pick up the bundle and start building the RTS game you’ve always wanted to play.&lt;/p&gt;&lt;h3 id="completeunity3dcdevelopercourse"&gt;&lt;a id="completeunity3dcdevelopercourse" href="https://youtu.be/5dwb0G0YxI4"&gt;Complete Unity 3D C# Developer Course&lt;/a&gt;&lt;/h3&gt;&lt;img&gt;&lt;img src="https://hb.imgix.net/76b1eb09b3a9a7808a34f6a23be5fb8a95e039db.jpg?auto=compress,format&amp;fit=clip&amp;h=350&amp;w=600&amp;s=651bca36078ed5d39f56f7dca67296b2"&gt;&lt;br&gt;&lt;p&gt;Ready to level up your game dev skills? Dive into our Unity 6 course and learn from the team that’s taught over a million students to code and build games. Unity is a powerful 3D engine, but it can feel like a boss fight for beginners. Don’t worry—we’ve got your back with step-by-step projects that make coding fun and easy.&lt;/p&gt;&lt;p&gt;You’ll create five games, each teaching you core skills. Dodge obstacles, blast aliens, and master everything from C# basics to advanced stuff like procedural generation and AI. Jump into projects like "Obstacle Dodge," "Rocket Boost," and "Sharp Shooter," where you’ll learn player controls, physics, AI, and more.&lt;/p&gt;&lt;p&gt;With clear guidance, lifetime access, and all files included, we make sure you’re set up for success. No coding experience? No problem—start from scratch and go pro in no time.&lt;/p&gt;&lt;p&gt;What are you waiting for? Dive into Unity 6 and start crafting your dream games!&lt;/p&gt;&lt;/div&gt;</description>
